rs%20ago%2C%20it%20seemed%20reasonably%20likely%20that%20a%20woman%20would%20be%20the%20next%20person%20to%20lead%20JPMorgan.%20As%20of%20Thursday%2C%20that%20seems%20a%20very%20slim%20possibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJPMorgan%20named%20Doug%20Petno%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftroy-rohrbaugh-jpmorgan-jamie-dimon-succession-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETroy%20Rohrbaugh%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20current%20co-heads%20of%20the%20bank's%20commercial%20and%20investment%20bank%2C%20as%20co-presidents%2C%20setting%20them%20up%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-jamie-dimon-ceo-succession-plan-senior-banker-promotions-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efrontrunners%20to%20succeed%3C%2Fa%3E%20longtime%20CEO%20Jamie%20Dimon.%20Their%20promotions%2C%20the%20bank%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release%2C%20%26quot%3Bare%20part%20of%20the%20Board's%20ongoing%20succession%20planning%20process.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPetno%20and%20Rohrbaugh%20were%20among%20a%20handful%20of%20powerhouse%20candidates%20poised%20to%20succeed%20Dimon%2C%20including%20Jennifer%20Piepszak%2C%20chief%20operating%20officer%2C%20Marianne%20Lake%2C%20CEO%20of%20the%20commercial%20bank%2C%20and%20Mary%20Erdoes%2C%20CEO%20of%20asset%20and%20wealth%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%2C%20in%20a%20mere%2018%20months%2C%20did%20the%20field%20narrow%20from%20predominantly%20women%20to%20all%20male%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjamie-dimon-career%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDimon%20has%20led%20JPMorgan%20%3C%2Fa%3Esince%202006%2C%20and%20his%20leadership%20during%20the%202008%20financial%20crisis%20cemented%20his%20status%20as%20one%20of%20the%20most%20trusted%20figures%20on%20the%20Street.%20Yet%20he%20celebrated%20his%2070th%20birthday%20this%20year%2C%20and%20questions%20about%20who%20would%20fill%20his%20shoes%20have%20circled%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Dimon%20underwent%20treatment%20for%20throat%20cancer%20in%202014%2C%20the%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reported%20that%20Erdoes%20was%20among%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdimons-two-top-potential-successors-2014-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etop%20two%20contenders%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20take%20over%2C%20should%20there%20be%20an%20immediate%20leadership%20change.%20Lake%20was%20also%20listed%20among%20the%20longer-term%20succession%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECome%202020%2C%20Citi%20announced%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fciti-jane-fraser-citigroup-transformation-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJane%20Fraser%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20become%20its%20CEO%2C%20making%20her%20the%20first%20woman%20to%20lead%20a%20major%20US%20bank.%20When%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F09%2F11%2Fbusiness%2Fdealbook%2Fwomen-wall-street-citigroup.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%20an%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20speculating%20which%20women%20might%20follow%20in%20Fraser's%20footsteps%2C%20Lake%20and%20Piepszak%20were%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20later%2C%20Piepszak%20became%20JPMorgan's%20chief%20operating%20officer%2C%20a%20promotion%20that%2C%20on%20its%20face%2C%20would%20have%20made%20her%20the%20most%20likely%20to%20succeed%20Dimon.%20Yet%20she%20said%20she%20had%20no%20interest%20in%20the%20job%2C%20effectively%20taking%20herself%20out%20of%20the%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20on%20Thursday%2C%20Lake%20did%20something%20similar%20by%20announcing%20her%20retirement%20after%20more%20than%2025%20years%20at%20the%20firm.%20That%20leaves%20Erdoes%2C%20whose%20position%20remains%20unchanged%2C%20according%20to%20the%20release.%20She%20wasn't%20mentioned%20in%20the%20part%20of%20the%20announcement%20explicitly%20about%20succession%2C%20and%20her%20name%20only%20came%20up%20in%20the%20last%20paragraph%20of%20the%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Lake's%20departure%20refigures%20the%20race's%20dynamics%2C%20it's%20not%20entirely%20surprising%20that%20Rohrbaugh%20and%20Petno%20emerged%20as%20front-runners.%20Erdoes%2C%20for%20one%2C%20runs%20a%20much%20smaller%20business%20than%20the%20two%20of%20them%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%20this%20year%2C%20the%20commercial%20and%20investment%20bank%20generated%20%249%20billion%20in%20net%20income%2C%20compared%20with%20%241.8%20billion%20in%20asset%20and%20wealth%20management.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20name%20came%20up%20in%20headlines%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeffrey-epstein-friends-settlements-victims-congress-house-oversight-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJeffrey%20Epstein%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20as%20the%20two%20exchanged%20emails%20when%20she%20was%20one%20of%20his%20primary%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-chase-drawn-out-breakup-with-jeffrey-epstein-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Econtacts%20at%20the%20bank%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There's%20no%20indication%20that%20her%20communications%20with%20Epstein%20have%20had%20any%20bearing%20on%20the%20succession%20race%2C%20and%20JPMorgan%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20matter.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20Thursday's%20announcement%2C%20women%20are%20still%20embedded%20in%20JPMorgan's%20innermost%20inner%20circle%20%E2%80%94%20seven%20of%20the%20people%20on%20the%20thirteen-person%20operating%20committee%20are%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20girlboss%2C%20it%20remains%20difficult%20for%20women%20to%20reach%20the%20highest%20echelons%20of%20Wall%20Street%2C%20still%20seen%20in%20many%20ways%20as%20a%2C%20if%20not%20the%2C%20boys'%20club.%20Last%20year%2C%20David%20Solomon%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20said%20the%20bank%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdavid-solomon-ceo-goldman-sachs-hiring-women-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehadn't%20made%20enough%20progress%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20elevating%20women%20to%20leadership%20roles.%20It%20appears%20that%20Fraser%20will%20remain%20the%20only%20woman%20leading%20a%20major%20US%20firm%20for%20the%20foreseeable%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDimon%20is%20uniquely%20embedded%20as%20a%20Wall%20Street%20leader%2C%20since%20investors%20laud%20his%20performance.%20Analysts%20from%20Bank%20of%20America%20said%20in%20a%20note%20that%20Lake's%20retirement%20suggests%20Dimon%20will%20remain%20CEO%20for%20several%20more%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20the%20departure%20of%20Lake%20%E2%80%94%20widely%20regarded%20in%20the%20industry%20as%20one%20of%20the%20best%20banking%20executives%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20loss%20no%20doubt%2C%20we%20believe%20the%20implication%20that%20the%20move%20indicates%20several%20more%20years%20of%20Dimon%20as%20CEO%20is%20a%20far%20bigger%20positive%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20note%20read.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWells%20Fargo%20banking%20analyst%20Mike%20Mayo%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20said%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bsurprised%20and%20puzzled%26quot%3B%20to%20see%20Lake%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%26quot%3Bstar%20executive%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20depart.%20But%20that's%20one%20cost%20of%20having%20a%20CEO%20as%20successful%20and%20long-tenured%20as%20Dimon.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20flip%20side%20is%20that%20JPMorgan%20%26quot%3Bmanufactures%20CEOs%2C%26quot%3B%20Mayo%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20next%20Marianne%20Lake%20is%20probably%20being%20groomed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-women-ceo-succession-race-dimon-rohrbaugh-petno-lake-2026-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782429039000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a3d9452360acd489560b8ce%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-wom